"So what did you call us for, Daryl?" Scarlett asked.

Right now, the succubus and the lamia were at an empty classroom. It was still noon. Scarlett sat in the chair one of the desks closest to the door, but she wasn't alone: Azure was also with her on the desk right at her side. Daryl had just arrived and her hand was still on the door knob.

She walked a few steps, stopping when she got in front of the desks where Azure and Scarlett were, her hands in her pockets.

"That was actually a few days ago, but I forgot to tell you two. Anyway. There's... some girl wanting to join the student council, I think? She was talking as if she was sure she would get in..."

"Is she aware that it's not something she can simply join like a club and that the whole student council is elected at once...?" Scarlett asked, confused.

"I... honestly don't know. She is a weirdo."

"Who is this girl?" The lamia did one more question.

"Konin. Do any of you know her?" The blonde girl nodded negatively.

"Ah... I think she is in my class. Is she the..." The mermaid tilted her head, thinking, and stopped her sentence before ending, unsure if she was right.

"The giant bunny girl." Daryl quickly replied.

"Y-yeah, I know her." With a expression of slight worry, the brunette answered. "She _is_ kind of weird..."

"Ahhh. I've heard of her, too." Scarlett had not much of a different reaction, though it was more subdued than Azure's, somehow. "I've never interacted with her, but gossip about the weird ones sure travel fast."

"That really doesn't surprise me, considering how she acts." The succubus did a small sigh. **"But what I wanted to tell you was basically that, I guess. So you aren't caught off-guard or anything."

"Hmm... We _are_ missing one person." Hand placed in her chin, Scarlett was thinking.

"Oi oi, Scarlett, ya can't—" Daryl quickly corrected herself, a bit embarrassed. "I-I mean, you can't seriously be considering her?"

"Well, as I said, we _are_ missing one person. The secretary." She said. "And rumors call her weird, sure, but she is pretty well-liked, as far as I heard. Can you confirm, Azure?"

"U-um, yes...!" A bit nervous with the attention of both of them going to her, the mermaid stuttered. "I-I think most consider her weirdness, umm, kind of endearing. I've also heard she got less weird with time. She is somewhat popular..."

"Hmm... What about her grades? People skills? Sociability?"

"Usually in the top five of our class, I think. She is, err, pretty good despite her lack of common sense? A-and she is very social." Azure paused for a second, hesitant because of Daryl's presence. "S-she's probably a better fit for the job than any of us...?"

"Oh, interesting." She seemed close to satisfied, but had one last question. "And she seems to truly like people, or...?"

"Seems to be genuine."

"Indeed, she'll do a better secretary than any of us. And unlike for us three, it won't be a living hell for her to do that job." And now, Scarlett was truly satisfied. "Well, she seems to be one of the better options we have, and if she has interest in being part of the student council, then it's perfect. I don't know what happened between you two, Daryl, but it's pretty much a fact that at the very least she'd seem like a good secretary for a student council. She increases our chances of being elected."

Daryl sighed. "I guess you're right... Ah, by the way. What if she simply doesn't show up? I don't know if she understands how our elections works."

"Then I'll scout her myself." The lamia replied.

"I thought you didn't want to scout anyone yourself...? Daryl said, a bit confused.

"I still don't, I still hate approaching people." She sighed. "But you don't want to go talk with her, do you? I'm not going to force Azure to go after her, either."

"Ah. Thanks, Scarlett." She smiled. "But it's okay, you can let me do it. It's not like I dislike her, it's just that she throws me off, kinda."

"Is it really alright?"

"Yep. Let me do it."

"If you say so. Thanks!~" She did a warm smile, completely unlike the mostly calm, almost expressionless demeanor she exhibited until now.

"...This throws me off, too." Daryl looked funny at Scarlett.

"Y-you get used to her swinging between, umm, both behaviors all the time." Azure did a chuckle, and then also looked at the lamia. "Force of habit again?"

"Yeah." Scarlett sighed. "I forget this trio of ours is safe and I just do this automatically. I wonder if with Konin here things will keep like this..."

"Eh, she seems harmless. If you act like this, she'll probably just say ya are cool and reminder her of some random yuri she read or whatever..." Daryl rolled her eyes for a second.

"Yuri...?" Scarlett asked, though her question didn't seem one of a confused person at all.

"Oh, if I had to sum it up... stuff about girls loving girls and dating, I guess?"

"A-ah, she knows what it is, Daryl..." Azure shyly said.

"Why is she asking 'yuri' like that, then?"

"I'm just kind of surprised she is into it, I guess." The lamia explained the reason of her answer. "Well, I've heard about some of her weirdness involving being sort of eager about lesbianism. I should've expected that."

"Oh, I see." She nodded as she understood what Scarlett was saying. Meanwhile, Azure meekly poked Scarlett's shoulder, who then tilted her head in Azure's direction, her ears attentive.

"Finally a kindred spirit for you, huh?" Azure whispered into Scarlett's ear, doing a somewhat mischievous smile.

"Shut up, Azu. I thought it was something important." She whispered back at Azure, who chuckled with her reply, and returned to looking at Daryl. Daryl looked at the two interacting, confused. "But is that it? Or is there something else to talk about?"

"Nah, just that. I'm probably going to go home after this, myself." The succubus replied. "It's pretty good that now our student council is finally fully assembled, though. That problem of ours was solved."

"Yep. Elections will start soon and it was really worrisome that we didn't have a secretary yet." Listening to the lamia speak, Azure quietly nodded along. "You'll try to invite her tomorrow, then?"

"Yeah. I'll speak with her as soon as I can."

"Good luck." She said calmly.

"Y-yeah, good luck." The mermaid was just going to nod again, but decided to say something this time.

"Thanks." Daryl chuckled and smiled, grateful. "Well, I'll be going then. Will you two stay or leave now too?"

"We will stay a bit longer. Right, Azu?" Scarlett looked at Azure when she said that. The mermaid nodded, confirming it.

"Okay, see ya." The succubus said, to which the lamia and the mermaid replied with a quiet wave, and went in the direction of the door.

Hands still in pockets, Daryl left the classroom.
